</P>
<P>
   ABC-VOICEMAIL-ADS (Undated) _ ABC has backed away from a
controversial plan to use sitcom stars like Norm MacDonald to
promote its fall lineup by leaving taped messages on viewers' home
answering machines. The decision came after the network, recently
known for aggressively seeking unusual new ways to promote its
programming, outlined the plan this week to reporters at an annual
fall-season briefing in Pasadena, Calif. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   AETNA-HMO (Undated) _ Call it bad luck, bad timing, bad judgment
or all of the above: Aetna, an old-line insurance company,
transformed itself into a hard-charging tightly managed health care
company four years ago, just in time to become a main target of a
backlash against managed care, especially the kind Aetna was
selling. By Milt Freudenheim.
