<P>
   FTC-PRIVACY (Washington) _ The Federal Trade Commission settled
its lawsuit against Toysmart.com, forbidding the bankrupt Internet
toy retailer from selling its database of personal customers
information, except under very limited circumstances.
</P>
<P>
   VOICESTREAM-DEUTSCHE (Hong Kong) _ For years, Li Ka-shing has
foraged in the darker corners of the telecommunications industry: a
paging service in Australia, an upstart mobile-phone operation in
Britain, a little-known provider of personal communications
services in Bellevue, Wash. Now that last company, VoiceStream
Wireless, is weighing a $53 billion takeover bid from Deutsche
Telekom. And Li may have found gold in another dark corner. By Mark
Landler.
</P>
<P>
   SAFRICA-AUSTRALIA-MINE (Johannesburg, South Africa) _
Anglo-American, the London-based South African mining giant, has
offered $1.8 billion for North Ltd. of Australia, one of the
world's biggest producers of iron ore. By Henri E. Cauvin.
