<HEADLINE>
MATTHAEUS SET TO REJOIN METROSTARS
</HEADLINE>
  c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ After a three-hour meeting at the league office in
Midtown Manhattan late Friday, the MetroStars and Major League
Soccer reached an agreement with Lothar Matthaeus that will keep
the German star with the MetroStars. The agreement came after two
tumultuous weeks following a back injury to the defender.
</P>
<P>
   Nick Sakiewicz, general manager of the MetroStars, said
Matthaeus would join the team for practice Wednesday and it would
be some time before he could start playing. The MetroStars play
host to the Miami Fusion Saturday afternoon and have a U.S. Cup
game against Tampa Bay on Tuesday on Long Island.
</P>
