<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBA-PETTITTE-SAMARITAN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PETTITTE GOES TO BOY'S AID IN STANDS
</HEADLINE>
  c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Andy Pettitte sprinted from right field just as
Yankees batting practice was ending. He saw that the fans in the
stands were more interested in screaming for autographs than in
attending to the fallen child around them.
</P>
<P>
   Pettitte saw the ball fly out of a batting cage and strike
12-year-old Rashad Harris in the left eye. Pettitte ran to the
seats behind the tarpaulin in right field and scooped the boy _ a
regular at batting practice who was without parents or guardians
Friday _ and flopped him onto his back.
</P>
<P>
   With a trail of concerned teammates behind him, Pettitte rushed
Rashad into the Yankees' clubhouse. Ten minutes later, the boy was
wheeled out of the Yankees' training room on a stretcher. He was
conscious, having responded to the questions of team doctors, but
he had a swollen eye and was taken to Columbia-Presbyterian Medical
Center.
</P>
</TEXT>
