nary a bulked-up SUV is to be found in his garage. He owns instead
two Rolls-Royces and a Porsche, partly because he worries more
about the danger of rolling over in a tall vehicle than he does
about auto theft.
</P>
<P>
   Americans may consciously or unconsciously fear crime when they
go for a drive, Rapaille said, but ``this is definitely not the
reality, it is the perception.''
</P>
