<SLUG> BC-R-AZERBAIJAN-RUSSIA-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IN THE NEW AZERBAIJAN, AN OLD FOX HANGS ON TO POWER 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Repeats to add art advisory.)  (ART ADV: Photo NYT 2 is being sent to NYT photo clients. Locator
map is being sent to NYT graphics clients. Nonsubscribers can
purchase one-time rights by calling 888-603-1036 or 888-346-9867.) 
 By DOUGLAS FRANTZ   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   BAKU, Azerbaijan _ President Heydar Aliyev of Azerbaijan, a wily
veteran of Soviet politics and of the KGB, has cautioned his
Russian counterpart, Vladimir Putin, a comparative political novice
who served the KGB in Russia and Germany, that he must deal with
