<P>
   FILLMORE-GROWTH (Fillmore, Calif.) _ A debate is under way over
the future of the tiny town of Fillmore, dividing those who want to
see a 1,000-home development - complete with golf course and
upscale homes - and those trying to preserve the city's Old
California way of life. Both sides will square off this fall when
competing ballot measures go before voters. By Joseph Giordono.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   PARAMEDIC-WORKLOAD (Los Angeles) _ Because the city of Los
Angeles is facing an ever-increasing shortage of paramedics,
paramedics are forced into working increasing amounts of overtime,
ofen in excess of 120 hours per week. To get a look at the problem
firsthand, we spend a day with a 26-year fire department veteran.
By Jordan Smith. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
