   WITH
</P>
<P>
   COLOMBIA-FARC _ SAN VICENTE, Colombia _ Fueled by tribute from
coca-growers and drug lords, the Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Colombia or FARC has become one of the most potent leftist
insurgencies in Latin American history. Ceded a Switzerland-sized
chunk of territory last year by Pastrana, the FARC shows no signs
of compromising in peace talks as they consolidate their control.
Profile of the group, its leaders, origins and history, set in San
Vicente, the capital of the rebel-held territory. WITH PHOTOS. With
map of map of Colombia and areas controlled by rebels and
coca-growing regions; chart of U.S. aid to Colombia over the past
decade.
</P>
