<P>
   VOTERS-SUBURBMOMS _ DATELINE TK _ Four years ago, ``soccer
moms'' gained almost mythical stature as the coveted voting bloc
that would reelect President Clinton or give Republican Bob Dole a
fighting chance. In a close presidential race in 2000 between Al
Gore and George W. Bush, the women's vote is all-important, but
more difficult to define and to attract. So far, polls are showing
that more men are strong supporters of their choice, where women
tend to be more flexible _undecideds or soft supporters of Gore or
Bush. In addition to the gender gap, there is a particularly large
``marriage'' gap. Clinton led Dole among married women 53% to 43%
in 1996; Gore trails Bush 42 percent to 50 percent. (Holmes, Cox
News Service)
