<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0722: CHINA CONNECTION _ Once a ``poor, backwards,
uneducated'' speck in the Henan province of China, in the words of
one local official, Sangpo is now a wired outpost. Its 4,800
residents boast private cars, cellular phones, about 100 personal
computers and a bustling Internet cafe. In 20 years, the village
has grown a sheepskin backyard business into a multi-million dollar
niche market. It now processes 5 million sheepskins a year, almost
half of China's total sheepskin imports. Technology has helped fuel
the growth. (Chao, Cox Washington Bureau) Art includes a 4-column
color photo of children working on computers, a 2-column photo of
workers using machinery, a 1-column photo of a company official and
a 3-column color photo of officials standing in front of
sheepskins.
