<P>
   CAR-TECH _ Video games, DVD players and even the PC are moving
out of the home and onto the road, which has made owning a simple
CD or cassette player for your set of wheels last century's news.
Luxuries usually strewn about the family room are becoming popular
gadgets in cars and in roomy SUVs. Ever since Oldsmobile introduced
a videocassette player for its minivans in 1998, car-stereo
enthusiasts have been adding more dazzle to audio systems with the
addition of video. And the automotive world is jumping the
bandwagon; every major manufacturer now offers video in the car.
(Dayton Daily News) WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
