   16.(x) WHITE TEETH, by Zadie Smith. (Random House, $24.95.)
</P>
<P>
   A chronicle of two families, encompassing 150 years,
</P>
<P>
   that revolves around an Englishman and a Bengali
</P>
<P>
   Muslim.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NONFICTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. THE DAY JOHN DIED, by Christopher Andersen. (Morrow,
</P>
<P>
   $26.) The events leading up to the plane crash that
</P>
<P>
   killed John F. Kennedy Jr., Carolyn Bessette Kennedy
</P>
<P>
   and Lauren Bessette.
</P>
<P>
   2. FLAGS OF OUR FATHERS, by James Bradley with Ron Powers.
</P>
<P>
   (Bantam, $24.95.) The story of the Marines who raised
</P>
<P>
   the flag at Iwo Jima, by the son of one of the men.
</P>
<P>
   3. TUESDAYS WITH MORRIE, by Mitch Albom. (Doubleday,
</P>
<P>
   $19.95.) A sportswriter tells of his weekly visits
</P>
<P>
   to his old college mentor, who was near death.
</P>
<P>
   4. ME TALK PRETTY ONE DAY, by David Sedaris. (Little,
</P>
<P>
   Brown, $22.95.) A collection of autobiographical comic
</P>
<P>
   essays by the author of ``Naked.''
</P>
<P>
   5.(x) IT'S NOT ABOUT THE BIKE, by Lance Armstrong with
</P>
<P>
   Sally Jenkins. (Putnam, $24.95.) A memoir by the Tour
</P>
<P>
   de France champion and cancer survivor.
</P>
<P>
   6. FROM DAWN TO DECADENCE, by Jacques Barzun.
</P>
<P>
   (HarperCollins, $36.) A survey of 500 years of
</P>
<P>
   Western cultural life, from 1500 to the present.
</P>
<P>
   7. IN A SUNBURNED COUNTRY, by Bill Bryson. (Broadway,
</P>
<P>
   $25.) The author of ``A Walk in the Woods'' reports
</P>
<P>
   on his travels through Australia.
</P>
<P>
   8. THE GREATEST GENERATION, by Tom Brokaw. (Random
</P>
<P>
   House, $24.95.) The lives of men and women who came
</P>
<P>
   of age during the Depression and World War II.
</P>
<P>
   9. IN THE HEART OF THE SEA, by Nathaniel Philbrick.
</P>
<P>
   (Viking, $24.95.) The story of the whale ship Essex,
</P>
<P>
   whose disastrous fate in the early 19th century
</P>
<P>
   would later serve as inspiration for Herman Melville.
</P>
<P>
   10. KITCHEN CONFIDENTIAL, by Anthony Bourdain.
</P>
<P>
   (Bloomsbury, $24.95.) A memoir-expose by the executive
</P>
<P>
   chef at Brasserie Les Halles in New York.
</P>
<P>
   11. PAPAL SIN, by Garry Wills. (Doubleday, $25.) A
</P>
<P>
   chronicle of what the author sees as the evasions and
</P>
<P>
   distortions of the Vatican over the past two centuries.
</P>
<P>
   12. DUTY, by Bob Greene. (Morrow, $25.) The columnist
</P>
<P>
   remembers his father, a soldier in World War II, and
</P>
<P>
   tells the story of Paul Tibbets, who piloted the
</P>
<P>
   plane that dropped the atomic bomb on Hiroshima.
</P>
<P>
   13. PAYNE STEWART, by Tracey Stewart with Ken Abraham.
</P>
<P>
   (Broadman &AMP; Holman, $24.99) A biography of the golfer
</P>
<P>
   who died in a plane crash in 1999, by his widow. (b)
</P>
<P>
   14.(x) HOW TO READ AND WHY, by Harold Bloom. (Scribner,
</P>
<P>
   $25.) The Sterling professor of humanities at Yale offers
</P>
<P>
   instruction in how best to read literary texts.
</P>
<P>
   15. THE ART OF HAPPINESS, by the Dalai Lama and Howard
</P>
<P>
   C. Cutler. (Riverhead, $22.95.) What Buddhism and common
</P>
<P>
   sense tell us about everyday problems.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ADVICE, HOW-TO AND MISCELLANEOUS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   1. WHO MOVED MY CHEESE? by Spencer Johnson. (Putnam,
</P>
<P>
   $19.95.) How to deal with changes at work and in life
</P>
<P>
   in general. (b)
</P>
<P>
   2. BODY FOR LIFE, by Bill Phillips with Michael D'Orso.
</P>
<P>
   (HarperCollins, $26.) Ways to improve one's body and
</P>
<P>
   one's life. (b)
</P>
<P>
   3. TEN THINGS I WISH I'D KNOWN _ BEFORE I WENT OUT INTO
</P>
<P>
   THE REAL WORLD, by Maria Shriver. (Warner, $19.95.)
</P>
<P>
   Life lessons from the anchorwoman. (b)
</P>
<P>
   4. SIMPLE ABUNDANCE, by Sarah Ban Breathnach. (Warner,
</P>
<P>
   $21.) Advice for women seeking to improve the way they
</P>
<P>
   look at themselves. (b).
</P>
<P>
   5. RELATIONSHIP RESCUE, by Phillip C. McGraw.
</P>
<P>
   (Hyperion, $22.95.) Reconnecting with one's
</P>
<P>
   partner. (b)
</P>
<P>
   6.(x) HEALTHY LIFE KITCHEN, by Marilu Henner with
</P>
<P>
   Lorin Henner. (ReganBooks/HarperCollins, $26.)
</P>
<P>
   A collection of recipes and kitchen tips.
</P>
